y. The contributors focus on three areas of inquiry-early modern era welfare policies for the poor, infrastructure, and forest management-to provide both a unique perspective on Japanese public finance at local levels and a vantage point outside of Europe to encourage a more global view of early modern political economies that shaped subsequent modern transformations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aPublic goodsxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh  acomparative study of premodern economies.  aearly modern era welfare policies.  aearly modern political economies.  aeconomic development in history.  aeurope and chinas economic history.  aforest management.  aglobal view.  aindustrialization.  ainfrastructure.  ajapan.  ajapanese public finance.  ajapanese socioeconomic history.  amarket economy.  amodern economic growth.  atokugawa era.1 aAihara, Yoshiyuki, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAoki, Takeshi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAratake, Kenichiro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBütow, Sascha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHealey, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIida, Takashi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaak, Heinrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanzaka, Junichi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKinoshita, Mitsuo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSakai, Kazuho, eco